<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1991) - "SOLID STATE" GLOW PLUG ANALYSIS GUIDE - GLOW PLUG FAILURE
        ANALYSIS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="4">
        <title>GLOW PLUG FAILURE ANALYSIS</title>
        <para>I. No visible damage, but glow plug may be electrically open Figure
            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600618">6.18</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef4600618" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg6178" filename="../figeg6/EG6178.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6.18 Glow Plug Tip Intact</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>II. Glow plug tip is missing. Figure
            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600619">6.19</hotlnk>
            Refer to CGED-470-* "7.3 Liter Engine Performance Analysis Guide" Test 9. An injection pump timing problem
            may exist.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef4600619" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg6179" filename="../figeg6/EG6179.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6.19 Glow Plug Tip Missing</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>III. Multiple "distorted" glow plug tips (Figure
            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600620">6.20</hotlnk>) require complete diagnostic analysis as specified on the front of
            form CGED-470-*.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef4600620" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="cg14754" filename="../figcg1/CG14754.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6.20 Glow Plug Tip Distorted</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>Warranty claims associated with the "Solid State" Glow Plug System, will not be accepted unless a
                    completed "Solid State' Glow Plug System Troubleshooting Guide" (CGED-470-*) is submitted with the
                    returned parts. (See Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4600621">6.21</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">* - Manual specified with latest revision</emph>
        </para>
        <figure id="ef4600621" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="cg13229" filename="../figcg1/CG13229.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6.21 Glow Plug Troubleshooting Guide</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>AFTER COMPLETING THE SOLID STATE GLOW PLUG TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE [CGED-470-*], AND NO PROBLEMS ARE
                    INDICATED; CONSIDER THE INSTALLATION OF THE 'GLOW PLUG CONTROLLER SENSING RESISTOR PACKAGE' [PART
                    NO. 1 813 444 C91] WHICH MAY IMPROVE STARTABILITY WITH AN ENGINE COLD COMPLAINT. FOLLOW THE
                    INSTRUCTION SHEET INCLUDED IN THE PACKAGE.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">* - Manual specified with latest revision</emph>
        </para>
